esqlQuery.esql:
// Alert when a pod has more than 10 distinct restarts within the time window.
//
// What triggers this alert:
// COUNT_DISTINCT(last_terminated_timestamp) > 10 — excessive container restarts.
//
// What it means:
// Pod in a crash loop or repeatedly failing — service disruption.
//
// Common causes:
// Application crashes, resource limits hit, liveness probe failures, dependency issues.
//
// Action needed:
// Check pod logs, review events, verify resource limits and health probes.
//
// Adjust threshold (e.g., 5 for stricter, 20 for more tolerant).
TS metrics-kubernetes.container-*
| WHERE `kubernetes.container.status.last_terminated_timestamp` IS NOT NULL
| STATS restart_count = COUNT_DISTINCT(`kubernetes.container.status.last_terminated_timestamp`)
  BY `orchestrator.cluster.name`, `kubernetes.pod.name`, `kubernetes.namespace`
| WHERE restart_count > 10
